","1390–Female":"1390–Deceased","1415–Male":"1415–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1287–Male":"1287–Deceased","1291–Female":"1291–Deceased","ABT    1330":"about 1330","abt 1390":"about 1390","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1291":"1291","1390":"1390","1415":"1415","1313":"1313","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","1287":"1287","about 1345":"about 1345","about 1313":"about 1313","about 1340":"about 1340","of,Tegeingl ctf,Flintshire,Wales":"Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Sandde Hardd, Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Plas Maen, Hope, Flintshire, Wales":"Hope, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of,,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Angharad","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old Celtic intensive prefix <i>an-</i> + <i>cār</i> ‘love’ + the noun suffix <i>-ad</i>. This was the name of the mother of the 12th-century chronicler  Giraldus Cambrensis  (‘Gerald the Welshman’). In the <i>Mabinogi</i>, Angharad Golden Hand at first rejects Peredur's suit, but later falls in love with him when he comes back as the unknown Mute Knight. The name has been strongly revived in Wales since the 1940s, borne, for example, by the actress  Angharad Rees  (  1949-2012 )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Angharad ferch Maredudd was born about 1313, in Hope, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Maredudd \" Bwl\" ap Dafydd, was 28 and her mother, Mrs. Maredudd Bwl ap Dafydd, was 24. She had at leas